= Introduction <ch:intro>

The central question of this project is whether a classical verifier with bounded computational resources can reliably certify that a quantum learner has produced a hypothesis meeting a specified accuracy guarantee @caro2025interactiveproofsverifyingquantum.

== Motivation <sec:motivation>

Quantum machine learning promises exponential speedups for certain learning tasks, yet verifying the output of a quantum computation from a purely classical standpoint remains an open challenge @mahadev2023classicalverificationquantumcomputations.

#lorem(200)

== Research Questions <sec:questions>

The primary research question asks under what conditions interactive proofs can be constructed so that a polynomial-time classical verifier gains confidence in the quantum learner's hypothesis.

